text_Basalt: each rock is very flatly colored and matte; there is not really shininess to any of them, and they look like they all have a fairly rough (as opposed to smooth) texture to their surface
text_Diorite: they are all speckled with highly-contrasting light and dark colors; they seem to have a little bit of subtle shininess to them and a rough surface texture

text_Basalt: they all have flat, matte coloration; they look like they have a rough surface texture but it seems to follow a particular direction, if that makes sense. some have holes that all seem to be going in the same direction through the rock
text_Gabbro: they all have a gently textured coloration, with subtle changes throughout the rock. they have a roughly textured surface that does not seem directional.

text_Basalt: they all have matte, flat coloration and a slightly rough surface.
text_Peridotite: all of these rocks have green at some point throughout them, and they look like they would sparkle at least a little bit in the light
